From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GitLab <gitlab@gitlab.com>
Date: Thu, 03 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] Increase heartbeat resilience for Ruby 3.3 thread
 scheduling

Ruby 3.3's M:N thread scheduler refactoring (bugs.ruby-lang.org issue
20816) causes increased context switching under GVL contention. With
high Sidekiq concurrency (>= 20 threads), the heartbeat thread can be
starved long enough for its Redis key to expire (60s TTL), silently
deregistering the process and halting all job processing.

This patch applies two complementary mitigations:

1. Increase Redis key TTL from 60s to 120s via HEARTBEAT_TTL constant
   (overrideable via SIDEKIQ_HEARTBEAT_TTL env var for operator control)
2. Elevate heartbeat thread priority to 3, with a rescue for platforms
   that do not support thread priorities

Combined effect: 2x missed beat capacity before deregistration
(6 beats -> 12 beats).

See: https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/issues/594030
---
 lib/sidekiq/launcher.rb | 14 ++++++++++++--
 test/launcher_test.rb   |  4 ++--
 2 files changed, 14 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/lib/sidekiq/launcher.rb b/lib/sidekiq/launcher.rb
--- a/lib/sidekiq/launcher.rb
+++ b/lib/sidekiq/launcher.rb
@@ -83,10 +83,14 @@ def heartbeat
 
     private unless $TESTING
 
-    BEAT_PAUSE = 10
+    BEAT_PAUSE = 10
+    HEARTBEAT_TTL = (ENV["SIDEKIQ_HEARTBEAT_TTL"] || 120).to_i
 
     def start_heartbeat
       Thread.current.priority = 3
+    rescue ThreadError, NotImplementedError
+      # Thread priorities are not supported on all platforms; ignore.
+    ensure
       loop do
         beat
         sleep BEAT_PAUSE
@@ -155,7 +159,7 @@ def heart
             transaction.unlink(work_key)
             if curstate.size > 0
               transaction.hset(work_key, curstate)
-              transaction.expire(work_key, 60)
+              transaction.expire(work_key, HEARTBEAT_TTL)
             end
           end
         end
@@ -175,7 +179,7 @@ def heart
               "rtt_us", rtt,
               "quiet", @done.to_s,
               "rss", kb)
-            transaction.expire(key, 60)
+            transaction.expire(key, HEARTBEAT_TTL)
             transaction.rpop("#{key}-signals")
           }
         }
diff --git a/test/launcher_test.rb b/test/launcher_test.rb
--- a/test/launcher_test.rb
+++ b/test/launcher_test.rb
@@ -50,7 +50,7 @@
       assert_in_delta 1000, rtt.to_i, 1000
 
       expires = @config.redis { |c| c.pttl(@id) }
-      assert_in_delta 60000, expires, 500
+      assert_in_delta 120000, expires, 500
     end
 
     it "fires start heartbeat event only once" do
@@ -77,7 +77,7 @@
       assert_equal ["1"], info
 
       expires = @config.redis { |c| c.pttl(@id) }
-      assert_in_delta 60000, expires, 50
+      assert_in_delta 120000, expires, 50
     end
 
     it "allows arbitrary proctitle extensions" do
